analysisPopulations.name: Intent-to-Treat Population
analysisPopulations.text: All randomized patients, whether or not the assigned study treatment was received
analysisPopulations.label: ITT
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: All randomized patients, whether or not the assigned study treatment was received

analysisPopulations.name: PD-L1-positive subpopulation
analysisPopulations.text: Patients in the ITT population whose PD-L1 status was IC1/2/3 at the time of randomization
analysisPopulations.label: PD-L1-positive
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: Patients in the ITT population whose PD-L1 status was IC1/2/3 at the time of randomization
analysisPopulations.criteria: ITT population AND PD-L1 status IC1/2/3 at randomization

analysisPopulations.name: Response-evaluable population
analysisPopulations.text: Patients in the ITT population with measurable disease at baseline
analysisPopulations.label: RE
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: Patients in the ITT population with measurable disease at baseline
analysisPopulations.criteria: ITT population AND measurable disease at baseline

analysisPopulations.name: PD-L1-positive response-evaluable population
analysisPopulations.text: Patients in the PD-L1-positive subpopulation with measurable disease at baseline
analysisPopulations.label: PD-L1+ RE
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: Patients in the PD-L1-positive subpopulation with measurable disease at baseline
analysisPopulations.criteria: PD-L1-positive subpopulation AND measurable disease at baseline

analysisPopulations.name: DOR-evaluable population
analysisPopulations.text: Patients in the ITT population with measurable disease at baseline and an objective response
analysisPopulations.label: DOR-evaluable
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: Patients in the ITT population with measurable disease at baseline and an objective response
analysisPopulations.criteria: ITT population AND measurable disease at baseline AND objective response

analysisPopulations.name: C-DOR-evaluable population
analysisPopulations.text: Patients in the ITT population with measurable disease at baseline and a confirmed objective response
analysisPopulations.label: C-DOR-evaluable
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: Patients in the ITT population with measurable disease at baseline and a confirmed objective response
analysisPopulations.criteria: ITT population AND measurable disease at baseline AND confirmed objective response

analysisPopulations.name: Patient reported outcome (PRO)-evaluable population
analysisPopulations.text: Patients in the ITT population with baseline PRO assessment and at least one post-baseline PRO assessment in the questionnaire of interest (European Organization for the Research and Treatment of Cancer [EORTC] Quality-of-Life Questionnaire [QLQ] C30, EORTC QLQ BR-23 or FACT-G).
analysisPopulations.label: PRO-evaluable
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: Patients in the ITT population with baseline PRO assessment and at least one post-baseline PRO assessment in the questionnaire of interest (European Organization for the Research and Treatment of Cancer [EORTC] Quality-of-Life Questionnaire [QLQ] C30, EORTC QLQ BR-23 or FACT-G).
analysisPopulations.criteria: ITT population AND baseline PRO assessment AND >=1 post-baseline PRO assessment

analysisPopulations.name: Safety-evaluable population
analysisPopulations.text: Patients who received any amount of any study drug
analysisPopulations.label: Safety
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: Patients who received any amount of any study drug
analysisPopulations.criteria: Received any amount of study drug

analysisPopulations.name: Pharmacokinetic (PK)-evaluable population
analysisPopulations.text: All patients who received any dose of study medication and who have at least one evaluable post-baseline PK sample
analysisPopulations.label: PK-evaluable
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: All patients who received any dose of study medication and who have at least one evaluable post-baseline PK sample
analysisPopulations.criteria: Received any dose of study medication AND >=1 evaluable post-baseline PK sample

analysisPopulations.name: Baseline ADA-evaluable population
analysisPopulations.text: All patients with at least one evaluable ADA assay result from a baseline sample
analysisPopulations.label: Baseline ADA
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: All patients with at least one evaluable ADA assay result from a baseline sample
analysisPopulations.criteria: >=1 evaluable ADA assay result from baseline sample

analysisPopulations.name: Post-baseline ADA-evaluable population
analysisPopulations.text: All patients with at least one evaluable ADA assay result from at least one post-baseline sample
analysisPopulations.label: Post-baseline ADA
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: All patients with at least one evaluable ADA assay result from at least one post-baseline sample
analysisPopulations.criteria: >=1 evaluable ADA assay result from >=1 post-baseline sample

analysisPopulations.name: China population
analysisPopulations.text: All patients enrolled in China (either in the global study or in the additional enrollment).
analysisPopulations.label: China
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: All patients enrolled in China (either in the global study or in the additional enrollment).

characteristics.name: Age
characteristics.description: Continuous variable summarized using means, SDs, medians, ranges, and interquartile ranges

characteristics.name: Region
characteristics.description: North America vs. Western Europe/Australia vs. Eastern Europe/Asia Pacific vs. South America
